CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 6A reads: "City Test? - Many residents of Webster Avenue near Blessing Street are wondering if the city is conducting a germ warfare test since this rubbish and debris have remained despite six weeks of complaints. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Trash, debris, and boxes piled on side of Webster Avenue near Blessing Street
